# UI tags and pills — sentence case

For **badges**, **pills**, **status tags**, **category chips**, and similar compact labels in the product UI (including Monitor agent activity, filters, and notifications):

- Use **sentence case**: capitalize only the **first letter of the phrase**; subsequent words are **lowercase** unless they are proper nouns, acronyms, or product names that must stay capitalized.
- **Do not** use title case for multi-word tags (avoid e.g. `Customer Interaction`; use `Customer interaction`).
- **Single-word** labels stay as one capitalized word when that reads naturally (e.g. `Success`, `Failed`, `Automation`, `Error`, `Processing`).

Keep **one convention** across category + status tags in the same surface so lists read consistently.
